WEBVTT

00:34.669 --> 00:36.804
Hello. My name is...

00:45.813 --> 00:46.781
Hi.

00:54.221 --> 00:55.557
Yeah.

01:01.763 --> 01:03.263
Hi. My name is...

01:26.821 --> 01:27.822
Ayar.

03:19.000 --> 03:20.535
No, no.

03:21.301 --> 03:22.837
No, she's related
to the old cleaning lady.

03:22.870 --> 03:25.540
She's a cousin or niece,
I don't know...

03:25.973 --> 03:28.776
Oh. No, I'm gonna make her
wear a mask and gloves.

03:28.810 --> 03:30.578
And she leaves
her clothes here after...

03:30.912 --> 03:32.747
He's fine. I mean, he actually,

03:32.780 --> 03:35.282
he made a ton of money
on some mask company.

03:35.717 --> 03:37.652
I know, it's so sad, but yeah.

03:38.820 --> 03:40.420
I should go. Yeah, okay,

03:40.454 --> 03:42.389
let's plan a play date
this weekend, okay?

03:42.422 --> 03:43.524
All right.

03:44.025 --> 03:45.727
I'm so sorry.

03:45.760 --> 03:47.327
I don't know where
my days get away from me now.

03:47.360 --> 03:48.696
- No problem.
- Sorry. Thanks for waiting.

03:56.070 --> 03:57.739
What is it?

03:57.772 --> 03:59.507
Sorry. Nothing. You're just...

03:59.540 --> 04:01.408
You're just so much younger
than I was expecting.

04:01.441 --> 04:02.810
How are you related

04:02.844 --> 04:04.444
- to Maria again?
- I'm not.

04:04.478 --> 04:05.980
She's my friend's mother.

04:06.013 --> 04:07.849
She told me
you just moved back from Vegas.

04:07.882 --> 04:09.684
Were you working at a hotel?

04:10.885 --> 04:12.687
I was working as a singer,

04:12.720 --> 04:14.387
but I came back
to be with my daughter.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.057
Your English
is really good.

04:16.090 --> 04:17.692
How long have you been here?

04:17.725 --> 04:19.259
Since I was thirteen.

04:21.495 --> 04:23.430
Well, the house is really big.

04:25.032 --> 04:26.868
Lots of rooms. Four bathrooms,
we only use two of them,

04:26.901 --> 04:28.870
so you have to clean
two every week.

04:29.704 --> 04:32.472
But we used to use
all the natural products,

04:32.507 --> 04:33.875
but they just honestly
don't get the job done,

04:33.908 --> 04:35.777
so now we just
use bleach on everything.

04:36.677 --> 04:38.913
We like the floors done,
the windows done weekly,

04:38.946 --> 04:41.015
laundry... you know?

04:41.516 --> 04:42.850
Sure. No problem.

04:42.884 --> 04:43.951
- Okay.
- Okay.

04:43.985 --> 04:45.052
Well.

04:45.686 --> 04:46.888
I can show you
where the supplies are,

04:46.921 --> 04:48.321
you can get started now.

04:48.623 --> 04:50.725
No, sorry. I can't start today.

04:50.758 --> 04:52.459
Oh, I thought we said today.

04:52.492 --> 04:53.861
No, we discussed Monday.

04:53.895 --> 04:56.531
We said on Monday.
I can start on Monday.

04:57.565 --> 04:58.900
Huh. Okay.

04:58.933 --> 05:00.701
Yeah, I guess that's fine.

05:00.735 --> 05:02.003
- Sure.
- All right.

05:02.036 --> 05:03.470
See you Monday.

05:21.856 --> 05:23.791
<i>Hey. How's L.A.?</i>

05:23.825 --> 05:25.526
<i>What do you want, Robert?</i>

05:25.860 --> 05:27.595
<i>I need to see you.</i>

05:27.628 --> 05:28.796
<i>When are you coming back, Ayar?</i>

05:29.063 --> 05:30.330
<i>I don't know.</i>

05:32.700 --> 05:34.569
<i>You're missing
some big auditions.</i>

05:35.970 --> 05:37.605
<i>I need to go.</i>

05:38.606 --> 05:39.674
<i>Please.</i>

05:40.440 --> 05:41.943
<i>I'm coming to see you.</i>

05:41.976 --> 05:43.878
<i>No.
Her birthday is today. Don't.</i>

05:44.879 --> 05:46.981
<i>Why are you doing this?</i>

05:47.615 --> 05:48.783
<i>I have to go.</i>

06:02.797 --> 06:03.965
I'll be there soon.

06:05.066 --> 06:06.067
<i>Oh, yeah,
you must be so excited</i>

06:06.100 --> 06:08.903
<i>to see her.
How long has it been?</i>

06:10.071 --> 06:11.105
Long.

06:13.107 --> 06:14.642
Too long.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.382
<i>You're back now.</i>

06:23.551 --> 06:24.752
<i>That's what matters.</i>

06:27.121 --> 06:29.557
I just hope it's not too late.

06:41.936 --> 06:43.871
Hey you!
Get away from there!

06:43.905 --> 06:46.173
What did you do with that? Stop!

06:47.174 --> 06:48.743
- Hey!
- You motherfucker.

06:48.776 --> 06:50.044
- You stop!
- Got you, motherfucker.

06:52.513 --> 06:53.781
You motherfucker.

06:54.181 --> 06:55.182
You motherfucker.

06:58.719 --> 06:59.754
Fuck.

07:53.607 --> 07:55.977
Can you believe that my daughter
won't even come here anymore?

07:58.546 --> 08:01.549
She could go to the bar, but she
can't come and see her mom.

08:10.057 --> 08:11.726
Ayar?

08:20.001 --> 08:20.968
Ayar?

08:25.673 --> 08:27.274
Hey.

08:28.909 --> 08:30.211
Who you looking for?

08:30.244 --> 08:32.179
No. No, I think
I'm in the wrong place.

08:33.014 --> 08:34.081
You sure?

08:34.749 --> 08:36.050
All good, thanks.
Have a nice day.

09:01.609 --> 09:03.711
<i>Sit straight.</i>

09:06.047 --> 09:08.315
<i>Sit proud.</i>

09:12.620 --> 09:14.055
<i>Look at you.</i>

09:15.890 --> 09:17.191
<i>So beautiful.</i>

09:51.959 --> 09:52.960
Hello?

09:55.796 --> 09:57.798
I know you're in there.
I just saw you at the window.

09:59.700 --> 10:02.036
I can hear you coughing.
Are you okay?

10:03.037 --> 10:05.773
I'm fine.
Just leave me alone.

10:14.215 --> 10:15.382
Raj!

10:18.886 --> 10:19.787
Raj!

10:20.754 --> 10:22.957
What? I was telling a story.
What happened?

10:41.375 --> 10:43.310
Did you put a sick person
next to my room?

10:43.344 --> 10:45.112
- What?
- Did you put someone with COVID

10:45.146 --> 10:46.981
- next to me?
- She said they had no symptoms

10:47.014 --> 10:48.149
- when they checked in.
- They said

10:48.182 --> 10:49.717
this wasn't a COVID motel.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.085
- It's not.
- Then why is the lady next door

10:51.118 --> 10:52.386
coughing her lungs out?

10:52.419 --> 10:53.988
She lied to me
when she checked in.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.690
By the time I'm back,
she'd better be

10:56.724 --> 10:58.225
far, far away from my room.

10:58.259 --> 11:00.861
- I will take care of it.
- Thanks. And please wear a mask.

11:00.895 --> 11:02.096
Will do.

11:03.197 --> 11:04.899
- Excuse me.
- Sorry, Ayar.

11:06.967 --> 11:08.135
Foster?

11:08.169 --> 11:09.370
Are you gonna move?

11:11.438 --> 11:12.773
Six feet!

11:12.806 --> 11:13.841
- Seriously?
- Yeah!

11:13.874 --> 11:15.342
That's a fancy top.

11:15.976 --> 11:18.212
- What's the occasion?
- None of your business.

11:18.245 --> 11:20.915
Why do I sense
you need someone to talk to?

11:20.948 --> 11:22.316
Hey, Raj!

11:22.750 --> 11:25.753
- You expecting some white dude?
- Hey!

11:25.786 --> 11:26.987
What was that earlier?

11:27.254 --> 11:28.322
With what?

11:28.355 --> 11:29.390
With the car.

11:30.157 --> 11:31.692
Uh, with that car?

11:31.892 --> 11:32.960
Uh-uh.

11:32.993 --> 11:35.129
I don't know. It's not my car.

11:38.766 --> 11:40.401
You should be wearing a mask!

11:41.068 --> 11:43.404
And you should mind
your fuckin' business.

11:49.410 --> 11:50.778
Shit.

11:53.480 --> 11:54.915
Shit.

11:58.986 --> 12:00.154
Okay.

12:20.908 --> 12:22.142
Julie.

12:22.176 --> 12:23.911
Oh. Finally.
Where have you been?

12:23.944 --> 12:25.279
I'm not late.

12:26.380 --> 12:27.748
What are you wearing?

12:28.849 --> 12:30.217
You hate it.

12:30.251 --> 12:31.852
No. You look pretty.

12:32.186 --> 12:33.521
You look like that girl in...

12:33.555 --> 12:35.856
- Oh!
- Go stand over there.

12:48.536 --> 12:49.903
Ta-daa!

12:49.937 --> 12:51.438
And I hope it's not stale.

12:56.110 --> 12:57.512
It's beautiful.

12:57.545 --> 12:59.446
Thank you. I love it.

13:00.281 --> 13:01.882
- Good.
- Thank you.

13:02.249 --> 13:04.251
It's time for you to finish it.

13:04.952 --> 13:06.086
What do you mean?

13:07.121 --> 13:08.789
Well, what do you
want to say to her?

13:22.336 --> 13:24.471
Please forgive me?

13:24.506 --> 13:26.240
What?

13:26.273 --> 13:28.375
I just think it's a little sad
for a birthday cake, no?

13:32.514 --> 13:34.048
- No, no, no, no!
- Let me cover it up.

13:34.081 --> 13:35.115
You're gonna ruin it.

13:36.884 --> 13:38.852
It looks great. It's perfect.

13:39.153 --> 13:40.487
It's just...

13:40.522 --> 13:42.056
- I'm so fucking nervous.
- Julie!

13:47.261 --> 13:48.395
What if she hates me?

13:49.664 --> 13:52.199
Don't be so hard on yourself,
you know,

13:52.567 --> 13:54.435
- just be honest with her.
- Julie! Now!

13:55.269 --> 13:56.904
Tell them to fucking wait!

13:59.507 --> 14:03.344
But now death
has come to our doorstep.

14:05.112 --> 14:07.515
You never listened before,

14:08.015 --> 14:09.983
so now you must be shown.

14:10.918 --> 14:13.487
Forget "when"
and ask yourself "what."

14:14.088 --> 14:15.422
Leave me alone, please.

14:15.456 --> 14:18.492
Oh this complicated,
distracting world,

14:18.526 --> 14:22.930
this man-made world
has led you astray.

14:23.263 --> 14:25.099
I asked you to leave me alone.

14:25.132 --> 14:26.900
You see, don't you?

14:27.334 --> 14:29.970
These selfish, deceitful dreams,

14:30.003 --> 14:34.576
these distracting storylines
made up by others.

14:34.975 --> 14:36.377
Leave me alone.

14:37.144 --> 14:39.446
<i>♪ We believed for too long ♪</i>

14:39.714 --> 14:42.316
<i>♪ That we could do anything ♪</i>

14:42.349 --> 14:44.451
<i>♪ Could be anyone ♪</i>

14:48.355 --> 14:52.926
<i>♪ ...than anyone
But at what cost? ♪</i>

14:53.193 --> 14:55.362
<i>♪ Is it possible that death ♪</i>

14:55.396 --> 14:57.030
<i>♪ The great equalizer ♪</i>

14:57.064 --> 14:59.366
<i>♪ Might somehow
Improve humanity? ♪</i>

14:59.734 --> 15:03.003
<i>♪ That this is
Our chance to reflect ♪</i>

15:03.036 --> 15:07.141
<i>♪ To right our wrong ♪</i>

15:12.112 --> 15:18.185
<i>♪ Happy birthday, dear Jasmine ♪</i>

15:18.218 --> 15:21.355
<i>♪ Happy birthday... ♪</i>

15:30.197 --> 15:32.266
Jasmine's hair's
getting so long.

15:36.103 --> 15:37.070
Jasmina?

15:37.672 --> 15:38.673
Come.

15:44.178 --> 15:45.647
Come here, sweetie.

15:57.090 --> 16:00.662
And you will have
the biggest party ever.

16:00.695 --> 16:03.263
What if I don't have
any friends by then?

17:16.838 --> 17:19.039
What the fuck?

17:43.430 --> 17:45.098
Is that Ayar?

18:13.828 --> 18:14.829
Where is she?

18:15.295 --> 18:17.497
Please. Don't do this.
Not today.

18:17.865 --> 18:19.132
What?

18:19.166 --> 18:20.768
I've canceled the party, Ayar.

18:23.337 --> 18:25.138
What are they
doing here, then, huh?

18:26.440 --> 18:28.175
It's not your decision.

18:28.208 --> 18:29.376
Let me in.

18:29.409 --> 18:30.678
- What...
- You're not coming in.

18:44.391 --> 18:45.727
Let me see her.

18:45.760 --> 18:47.260
I just wanna see her.

18:52.567 --> 18:55.268
That's my daughter.
She's still my daughter.

19:01.743 --> 19:03.210
What did you tell her?

19:16.791 --> 19:18.760
Jasmine!

19:18.793 --> 19:20.193
Jasmine!

19:20.862 --> 19:22.429
- Jasmine!
- Stop doing this!

19:22.462 --> 19:23.463
- Stop!
- Jasmine!

19:23.497 --> 19:24.498
You stop it! You stop it!

19:29.469 --> 19:30.705
I've been back for two weeks.

19:30.738 --> 19:31.939
Two weeks,
and I haven't seen her.

19:31.973 --> 19:32.907
- Two weeks?
- Yes.

19:32.940 --> 19:34.174
- Two?
- Yes.

19:38.613 --> 19:40.347
Why are you
doing this to me, mom?

19:42.349 --> 19:43.350
Mom?

19:51.993 --> 19:53.561
You wanted me to.

19:53.594 --> 19:54.762
You said you wanted
to take care of her.

20:07.041 --> 20:08.943
What do you really want, Ayar?

20:09.977 --> 20:11.278
Why now?

20:20.588 --> 20:22.322
I just wanted to see her.

20:39.439 --> 20:40.775
I'm not a bad person.

20:40.808 --> 20:42.744
But you're a stranger to her.

20:44.912 --> 20:46.614
This will take time.

20:47.715 --> 20:49.282
And you must learn.

20:52.687 --> 20:54.454
From who? From you?

20:56.524 --> 20:57.525
From her.

21:09.570 --> 21:10.470
Here.

21:10.872 --> 21:12.272
Just give her this.

21:13.708 --> 21:15.710
Just give her this. Please.

22:38.059 --> 22:41.095
]

23:18.666 --> 23:20.167
Did you have a nice day?

23:22.236 --> 23:23.838
Who was that today?

24:19.994 --> 24:21.162
But your mother,

24:22.697 --> 24:24.732
she remembered everything.

24:26.100 --> 24:28.636
She answered all the questions.

24:32.640 --> 24:34.075
Sit straight, please.

24:38.679 --> 24:40.014
Sit straight.

24:40.548 --> 24:41.582
Why?

24:42.850 --> 24:44.618
Now you look strong.

24:46.320 --> 24:47.688
So beautiful.

24:49.123 --> 24:51.826
Why didn't you let
Mommy come in today?

25:03.571 --> 25:05.673
From where
our ancestors come from.

25:05.973 --> 25:06.941
Where is it?

25:07.308 --> 25:09.276
Now we call it Cuzco.

25:17.218 --> 25:20.087
Now in the highest
mountains of all...

25:31.665 --> 25:33.834
...where the most supreme god

25:33.868 --> 25:35.936
gave birth to four sons.

25:36.704 --> 25:37.972
Why?

25:40.207 --> 25:42.276
You can decide
how much of it's true.

25:42.843 --> 25:43.844
Okay.

25:44.178 --> 25:46.881
Now listen, the gods

25:46.914 --> 25:50.117
bestowed them
with a golden stick...

25:59.093 --> 26:00.861
He was so strong.

26:09.270 --> 26:11.705
...and buried him in stone.

26:18.312 --> 26:22.716
...and they encountered
a stone deity.

26:28.889 --> 26:31.659
...except one brother.

26:32.693 --> 26:35.663
He wanted to show
he was the strongest

26:35.696 --> 26:37.331
by defying it,

26:37.364 --> 26:39.066
and when he touched it,

26:39.934 --> 26:42.203
he turned to stone.

26:43.804 --> 26:46.006
Now there was the third brother.

26:55.783 --> 26:59.320
But when he thought
he'd found the perfect land,

27:00.387 --> 27:04.191
he turned to stone.

27:05.726 --> 27:07.928
Now, there was one brother left.

27:15.436 --> 27:17.204
...continued on their path.

27:17.238 --> 27:19.974
And when they
finally arrived in Cuzco,

27:20.441 --> 27:24.311
he sunk the golden stick
into the ground.

27:25.379 --> 27:26.847
His name was

27:27.781 --> 27:29.783
Ayar Manco.

27:30.184 --> 27:31.819
That's Mommy's name.

27:33.020 --> 27:34.021
Yes.

27:34.822 --> 27:36.957
So with his own hands...

27:40.461 --> 27:42.163
And when he was done,

27:42.897 --> 27:44.431
he turned to stone.

27:46.800 --> 27:49.703
And now rests with nature.

27:52.006 --> 27:53.007
Good night.

27:54.208 --> 27:57.178
They should have worked together
like a family's supposed to.

27:58.746 --> 27:59.880
Perhaps.

28:00.414 --> 28:03.017
Is Mommy gonna turn to stone?

28:03.784 --> 28:04.885
No.

28:05.219 --> 28:06.253
Don't worry.

28:06.754 --> 28:07.955
Is she sick?

28:08.289 --> 28:09.290
No.

28:15.362 --> 28:17.264
What if it doesn't pass?

28:19.433 --> 28:20.434
It will.

28:21.101 --> 28:22.703
How do you know?

28:54.001 --> 28:55.469
Like in the movies.

29:58.566 --> 30:03.237
Dear, you can be
anything you dream of.

30:04.539 --> 30:06.373
You can be anything.

30:09.544 --> 30:13.013
<i>♪ I am here, here I am ♪</i>

30:13.047 --> 30:15.849
<i>♪ I remember my first love ♪</i>

30:15.883 --> 30:18.586
<i>♪ There's a new girl in town
So look out everyone ♪</i>

30:40.407 --> 30:43.077
Cadence isn't
just about your voice.

30:43.110 --> 30:44.178
It's about movement.

30:49.149 --> 30:50.884
Do you feel that pain?

30:51.452 --> 30:53.253
You can use that pain.

30:53.287 --> 30:54.556
You can build on it.

31:30.023 --> 31:31.024
Hey?

31:33.394 --> 31:34.428
Are you okay?

31:38.198 --> 31:40.000
Do you need any help?

31:48.710 --> 31:51.412
Hey!

32:05.192 --> 32:07.394
Raj!

32:11.064 --> 32:12.032
Raj!

32:19.373 --> 32:20.608
Raj!

32:29.751 --> 32:31.719
No, I was joking.

32:31.753 --> 32:34.488
Let me tell you a story,
when I was seventeen,

32:34.522 --> 32:36.724
about my grandma in Jaipur.

32:36.758 --> 32:38.992
Beautiful city in Rajastan,
you must visit.

32:39.561 --> 32:42.296
- I'm almost done.
- Oh, good.

32:42.597 --> 32:43.964
My grandma,

32:45.098 --> 32:46.768
bless her Hindi heart,

32:46.801 --> 32:48.368
she told me this

32:48.402 --> 32:50.738
the day before
I moved to America.

32:51.506 --> 32:54.676
She said one middle of the night

32:54.709 --> 32:56.443
she woke up

32:56.477 --> 32:58.145
and went straight to the kitchen

32:58.178 --> 33:01.181
and grabbed the longest knife
she could find,

33:01.215 --> 33:03.450
and walked back
to my grandfather's bed,

33:03.484 --> 33:06.320
and stood there
with the knife in her hands.

33:06.353 --> 33:07.689
She was sleepwalking?

33:07.722 --> 33:10.390
She stood there for entire hour,

33:10.424 --> 33:12.159
holding the knife
above his chest,

33:12.459 --> 33:15.162
and then
returned back to the kitchen

33:15.195 --> 33:17.064
and went back to sleep.

33:17.297 --> 33:18.298
He abused her.

33:18.332 --> 33:19.767
I'm sure.

33:19.801 --> 33:22.202
To Americans,
most Indian women are abused.

33:22.570 --> 33:26.306
She said every night
she would grab the knife

33:26.340 --> 33:29.309
and hold it above him
when he's asleep,

33:29.343 --> 33:32.346
and wait for gods to show
some sign to plunge

33:32.379 --> 33:33.648
the knife in his chest.

33:33.681 --> 33:35.115
Oh, shit.

33:35.148 --> 33:37.785
She looked at me
straight in the eyes

33:38.485 --> 33:41.154
and said, "Remember, Raj,

33:41.188 --> 33:43.591
one day,
you are going to get married,

33:43.625 --> 33:46.226
and you'll be sleeping
next to your own wife."

33:47.595 --> 33:49.396
You know,
the divorce rate in India

33:49.429 --> 33:51.098
- is less than one percent.
- Raj!

33:51.131 --> 33:52.667
- Much lower than the...-
- Raj!

33:52.700 --> 33:54.434
- Why is she still here?
- Someone always

33:54.468 --> 33:56.504
- interrupts my thoughts.
- She's still in her room!

33:56.538 --> 33:58.205
- Who?
- Who do you think?

33:58.238 --> 33:59.674
- The sick woman.
- No one is there. She's gone.

33:59.707 --> 34:01.709
- No one is there.
- She was just coughing.

34:02.242 --> 34:04.378
- What are you talkin' about?
- I just heard her.

34:04.612 --> 34:08.181
I helped to call an ambulance.
She was very sick.

34:08.650 --> 34:10.785
And I saw them load her up.

34:27.569 --> 34:28.836
